definition: see 莎草[suo1 cao3]/see 摩莎[mo2 suo1]

sentences.english: Competition on growth between Juncellus serotinus and Sagittaria pygmaea was evident.
sentences.chinese: 水莎草与矮慈姑两种杂草间也存在生态竞争关系。

sentences.english: Many of the papyri had not been read for over a thousand years.
sentences.chinese: 很多的纸莎草纸一千多年来都没有被解读。

sentences.english: grass-like species such as Pennsylvania sedge take over.
sentences.chinese: 宾夕法尼亚莎草之类的草类物种接管了领地。

sentences.english: Then the Berkeley Sedge grew, and grew.
sentences.chinese: 随后，伯克利莎草开始不停地长啊，长啊。

sentences.english: A long torn twisted strip of papyrus, on which a column of Greek letters are written.
sentences.chinese: 一长条扭曲破裂的纸莎草纸，上面写着一排希腊字母。

sentences.english: He is holding a partially rolled papyrus scroll in his left hand.
sentences.chinese: 他是持有部分滚动推出的莎草纸在他的左手。

sentences.english: The building and boardwalks frame the rain gardens and broom sedge meadows.
sentences.chinese: 建筑与木栈道环绕着雨水花园与郁郁葱葱的莎草地。

sentences.english: Like a lot of typical intertropical plants, paper nutgrass flatsedge is very sensitive to frost.
sentences.chinese: 像许多典型的热带植物一样，纸莎草对霜很敏感。

sentences.english: Woollen cloth and timber were sent to Egypt in exchange for linen or papyrus .
sentences.chinese: 羊毛料和木材送到埃及以换取亚麻布或纸莎草纸。

sentences.english: Manage your busy life with Papyrus and your mobile phone.
sentences.chinese: 忙碌的生活与纸莎草纸管你和你的手机。
